тЬУ Spec (7 criteria тАФ 7 verifiable):
  тЬУ Default behavior is unchanged: when `preserveConsecutiveUppercase` is not provided (or is `false`), every existing test case produces the same output as before тАФ e.g. `camelCase('FOO-BAR')` тЖТ `'fooBar'`, `camelCase('XMLHttpRequest')` тЖТ `'xmlHttpRequest'`, `camelCase('FOO')` тЖТ `'foo'`, `camelCase('FBBazzy')` тЖТ `'fbBazzy'`, `camelCase('FOO', {pascalCase: true})` тЖТ `'Foo'`.
  тЬУ A `preserveConsecutiveUppercase` boolean option is accepted by `camelCase()`. When set to `true`, consecutive-uppercase runs (2+ uppercase letters in a row) in the input are kept uppercase in the output instead of being lowercased and re-capitalized. For example: `camelCase('foo-BAR', {preserveConsecutiveUppercase: true})` тЖТ `'fooBAR'` (not `'fooBar'`); `camelCase('foo-BAR', {preserveConsecutiveUppercase: true, pascalCase: true})` тЖТ `'FooBAR'` (not `'FooBar'`).
  тЬУ `preserveConsecutiveUppercase` works together with the `pascalCase` option. When both are `true`, the first character is uppercased AND consecutive-uppercase runs are preserved тАФ e.g. `camelCase('FOO-BAR', {preserveConsecutiveUppercase: true, pascalCase: true})` keeps the uppercase runs rather than normalizing them to `'FooBar'`.
  тЬУ The test file contains dedicated tests for `preserveConsecutiveUppercase: true` covering both camelCase and pascalCase modes, with multiple inputs that include consecutive-uppercase runs (e.g. all-caps words like `FOO`, acronyms like `XML`/`HTML`/`URL`, mixed like `myURLstring`, and separator-joined like `FOO-BAR`).
  тЬУ The TypeScript definition file (`index.d.ts`) declares `preserveConsecutiveUppercase` as an optional boolean property on the `Options` interface, with a default of `false`.
  тЬУ `npm test` passes with exit code 0, including all original tests and all new `preserveConsecutiveUppercase` tests.
  тЬУ When `preserveConsecutiveUppercase` is `false` (or omitted), the output is identical to the pre-change behavior for every input тАФ the option introduction does not alter any code path when the option is not active.
